Text.Value: Halsin's dead. I thought you'd want to know.
Absolute... Moonrise Towers...
Halsin's dead. Is there any other way to get rid of a mind flayer parasite?
Wanted to protect... wanted to give... mercy...
How can I get rid of a mind flayer parasite?
Leave.
Master Halsin... studied parasites... hunted the source...
How can I get rid of the mind flayer parasite?
Find Halsin... knows parasites... studied them...
Where did you keep your valuables?
Wolf Rune... Rath...
What happened to you?
And how do I get past these locks?
*The corpse says nothing. Its dead eyes convey no pain, only acceptance.*
Nettie... apprentice healer... to Master Halsin...
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
My circlet...
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
Where is Halsin?
Who are you?
Tried to protect... our grove...
Where is Halsin?

EditorData.logicalname: PC knows about Halsin already, Nettie doesn't have to mention him first

Text.Value: *The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
Went to goblins... never came back...
*The corpse seems willing to speak - but not to its killer.*
Gone... with adventurers...
How do I get out of this room?
Beneath... locked by runes...

Synopsis: Speak with Dead dialog with Nettie, Halsin's apprentice. Nettie likely died while trying to kill the player by poisoning them. She didn't want to, but did it to protect the grove, knowing that you might transform into a monster that would kill everyone there.
